uilds increases switching cost and makes the platform stickier.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":7,\"impact\":10,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T12:09:18.325Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T12:09:18.325Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":8,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
[2026-03-18T12:09:27.163Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01W1PXBUxGLvKsp4LackoeoM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NZt8LMoJGkG2t79uC9GjC5","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"d4eaed24-44dd-47f1-afe3-1b8702a903b2\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"tech_innovator\",\n    \"category\": \"performance\",\n    \"title\": \"In-memory subscription routing table with hot reload\",\n    \"description\": \"Every eventBusTick calls getSubscriptionsByEventType() which runs a SQLite query per event, then matchEvent() filters in JS. With N events and M subscriptions this is O(N) DB queries plus O(N*M) JS filtering per 2s tick. Build an in-memory inverted index Map of eventType to Subscription array loaded at startup and incrementally updated via change-detection hooks on subscription CRUD endpoints in httpApi.ts. Event matching becomes a single hash lookup O(1) per event type with no DB round trip. Combined with payload filters this index could also pre-compile JSONPath expressions into cached matchers amortizing parse cost across thousands of events. Spike: Build SubscriptionIndex class with load/update/lookup methods, wire into eventProcessor replacing getSubscriptionsByEventType calls, benchmark with 200+ subscriptions. Risk: Index can become stale if subscriptions are modified by external processes; needs periodic reconciliation sweep.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"The DB-per-event subscription lookup is the hidden multiplier in the N+1 cascade meaning event processing throughput is inversely proportional to event volume. An in-memory index inverts this: throughput becomes independent of subscription count, and the system handles 10x event volume with zero additional DB load. This creates a compounding advantage as the platform grows because more subscriptions and more events make the index MORE valuable while the alternative (DB queries) degrades.\",\n    \"effort\": 7,\n    \"impact\": 9,\n    \"risk\": 6\n  }'","description":"Submit idea 4: In-memory subscription routing table"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":195,"cache_read_input_tokens":65848,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":195},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"782e4324-9122-4bd8-ac29-f35468e2642b","uuid":"4643494d-10ac-46c7-9bde-a39d27c198df"}
